,” our “hurrying, crashing, sad, distracted year.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAmerican literature. 0aAmerican poetry. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  apoetry, collection, creative writing, literature, war, death, complicity, value, history, politics, morality, homefront, philosophy, science, military, soldier, violence, drone, weapons, contemporary, invasion, conquest, occupation, peace, civilians, bombing, terrorism, citizenship, empire, oil, america, fear, bias, discrimination, islamophobia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226289793423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226289793/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles